  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, and ginger, and cook until the onion is translucent.",
    "Add the coriander seeds, cumin seeds, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the red lentils and 4 cups of water, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes, or until the lentils are tender.",
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Transfer the lentil mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish, and top with feta cheese.",
    "Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Sprinkle with chopped fresh parsley, and serve hot on a wooden board."
  ],
